<p>I have a code which extracts the information from the active outlook folder. Now I need to filter the results using the following criteria.</p>  <ol> <li><p>I want the user to put the email on the inputbox and it automatically selects the folder from outlook (even if it is not the active folder or not)</p></li> <li><p>Filter he date range for the extract "myItem.ReceivedTime" is for all emails. Is it possible to create a filter for specific date range? the start and end date will be based on the user's input on cells C1,D1</p></li> </ol>  <p>Thanks in advance</p>  <pre><code>    Sub ExtractOutlookFields()     On Error Resume Next     Set myOLApp = Outlook.Application     Set myNamespace = myOLApp.GetNamespace("mapi")     Set myfolder = myOLApp.ActiveExplorer.CurrentFolder     Set xlobj = CreateObject("excel.application.14")     xlobj.Visible = True     xlobj.Workbooks.Add      xlobj.Range("a" &amp; 1).Value = "Sender"     xlobj.Range("b" &amp; 1).Value = "Subject"     xlobj.Range("c" &amp; 1).Value = "Recieved time"     xlobj.Range("d" &amp; 1).Value = "Categories"     xlobj.Range("e" &amp; 1).Value = "Flags"      For i = 1 To myfolder.Items.Count     Set myItem = myfolder.Items(i)      xlobj.Range("a" &amp; i + 1).Value = myItem.SenderName     xlobj.Range("b" &amp; i + 1).Value = myItem.Subject     xlobj.Range("C" &amp; i + 1).Value = myItem.ReceivedTime     xlobj.Range("d" &amp; i + 1).Value = myItem.Categories     xlobj.Range("e" &amp; i + 1).Value = myItem.Flags     Next     End Sub </code></pre>